---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import LinkButton from '../components/LinkButton.astro';
---

<Layout title="Research" description="Research interests and learning directions.">
  <article class="article">
    <p class="eyebrow">Research</p>
    <h1>Research Directions</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      This page is kept as a lightweight place for research directions and reading paths. It is not part of the main
      navigation for now.
    </p>

    <h2>Current Directions</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Vision-Language-Action Models</li>
      <li>Embodied AI</li>
      <li>Robot learning</li>
      <li>Robot control</li>
      <li>AI-assisted research workflows</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Reading Path</h2>
    <p>
      Detailed reading notes and learning paths now live in Notes. I will use this space when a research direction
      becomes mature enough to organize separately from general notes and project pages.
    </p>
    <div class="link-row">
      <LinkButton href="/notes/" label="Notes" />
      <LinkButton href="/notes/paths/embodied-ai-vla/" label="Embodied AI / VLA" />
      <LinkButton href="/notes/paths/robotics-foundations/" label="Robotics Foundations" />
      <LinkButton href="/notes/paths/ai-assisted-research-workflow/" label="AI-assisted Workflow" />
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
